# Generated Story Output

Apply this rule only when the current project is a design-system Storybook repo whose package name matches `@kyndryl-design-system/shidoka-*`. Ignore this rule in consuming apps.

For those design-system repos, generated Storybook page files must be written to:

- `src/stories/generated/Page1.stories.js`
- `src/stories/generated/Page2.stories.js`
- `src/stories/generated/PageN.stories.js`

Rules:

- Do not create generated page stories in `generated/pages/`, `src/stories/generated-pages/`, or top-level `src/stories/`.
- Use `Page1`, `Page2`, etc. for both the filename stem and the named story export.
- Keep generated page stories as `.stories.js` files unless the user explicitly asks for a different extension.
- Treat files in `src/stories/generated/` as ephemeral outputs, not canonical design references.
- Do not use existing generated pages as the design authority when generating a new page; use the Shidoka Studio MCP payload and page-generation rule instead.
- When correcting an existing generated page the user points to, update it in place inside `src/stories/generated/` instead of creating a second copy somewhere else.
